     "text": [
      "Based on the provided context, here are some key changes in The Coca-Cola Company's marketing strategy over the last year:\n",
      "\n",
      "1. **Global focus**: The company is adapting to varying market dynamics by leveraging its global scale and stepping up local execution (Source: [19]).\n",
      "2. **Emphasis on value share gains**: The company has been investing behind its brands, leading to value share gains and revenue and profit growth (Source: [19]).\n",
      "3. **Increased focus on affordability and premiumization**: The company is reprioritizing investments to drive affordability through refillables and premiumization through single-serve offerings (Source: [20]).\n",
      "4. **Digital customer platforms**: The company is scaling connected packaging and its digital customer platforms to drive transactions (Source: [20]).\n",
      "5. **Activation of Share a Coke campaign**: The company launched the iconic Share a Coke campaign across over 120 countries, with personalized names on approximately 10 billion bottles and cans (Source: [4]).\n",
      "6. **Tailoring campaigns to regional and local needs**: The company is developing more granular channel and customer-specific execution strategies, driving more tailored promotional campaigns (Source: [20] and [47]).\n",
      "7. **Increased focus on localness of the system**: In Eurasia and the Middle East, the company emphasized its mix of local and global brands and highlighted the localness of its system (Source: [38]).\n",
      "8. **Investment in AI and Agentic tech**: The company plans to bring in AI and Agentic tech over the coming years to drive ongoing productivity (Source: [47]).\n",
      "\n",
      "These changes reflect a shift towards more targeted, digital, and customer-centric marketing strategies, as well as an increased focus on driving value share gains and top-line revenue growth.\n",
      "sources: [19, 20, 4, 53, 38, 47]\n"
     ]
